results.name: Decimal expansion of A060295^6.
comment: A large near-integer obtained by taking the Ramanujan constant e^(Pi*sqrt(163)) to the sixth power. The constants for even higher powers are in general no longer near integers.
reference: Henri Cohen, A Course in Computational Algebraic Number Theory, 3., corr. print., Springer-Verlag Berlin Heidelberg New York, 1996 pp. 383.
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 105..10000
results.author: _Mark A. Thomas_, Oct 16 2009
ext: Formula edited and connected to other powers by _R. J. Mathar_, Feb 27 2010
